dct_description_sm: From British Surveys ; Published April 1875 at the Hydrographic Office, Washington D.C. ; R. H. Wyman Commo. U.S.N. Hydrographer to the Bureau of Navigation.
Hachure and spot-height relief with lines and soundings showing depths.
Shows railways, land routes, lights, visibility from various points, buoys, low water areas, coastal relief and place names (harbors, coves, points, bays, waterways, etc.)
[Inset map] St. Paul I. / Surveyed by Captain H. W. Bayfield, R.N.m 1836
